<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="81" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Conservation status in Cameroon.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="81">
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. E. Hess, Ber. Geobot. Inst. Eidg. Techn. Hochsch. Stiftung Rŭbel Heft 32: 188" authorityYear="1961" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Podostemaceae" genus="Dicraeanthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dicraeanthus zehnderi" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zehnderi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Dicraeanthus zehnderi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was listed on http://www.iucnredlist.org as Critically Endangered (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2010-3.RLTS.T185600A8444300.en" author="Ghogue, J-P" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B31" refString="Ghogue, J-P, 2010c. Dicraeanthuszehnderi. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e.T185600A8444300. https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2010-3.RLTS.T185600A8444300.en" title="Dicraeanthuszehnderi. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species 2010: e. T 185600 A 8444300." url="https://doi.org/10.2305/IUCN.UK.2010-3.RLTS.T185600A8444300.en" year="2010 c">Ghogue 2010c</bibRefCitation>
). It was also assessed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Onana, JM" journalOrPublisher="Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" refId="B66" refString="Onana, JM, Cheek, M, 2011. Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments. Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew" title="Red data list of the flowering plants of Cameroon: IUCN Global Assessments." year="2011">Onana and Cheek (2011)</bibRefCitation>
as Critically Endangered since it has not been collected for many decades. The only known collecting locality for 
<taxonomicName genus="D." lsidName="D. zehnderi" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" rank="species" species="zehnderi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">D. zehnderi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the waterfall on Sanaga River at Edea. The extent of occurrence and the area of occupancy are both estimated at 4 km2. The hydropower dam on the waterfall will adversely affect the survival of this species and other 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Podostemaceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Podostemaceae" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="genus">Podostemaceae</taxonomicName>
species present at this locality. The taxon is here reassessed as Critically Endangered. IUCN Red List Category: 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81">Critically Endangered CRB1+2ab (iii).</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
